%T A396917 3314,3368,3840,4682,4736,4772,5512,5672,6002,6124,6640,7128,7152
%N A396917 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<y<=z<=t<=w such that  sigma(x)^2*psi(x)*phi(x) = x^4 + y^4 + z^4 + t^4 + w^4.
%C A396917 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma^2*psi*phi-quartic quintuple.
%H A396917 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-2-psi-phi-quartic-quintuples/blob/main/A396917">Python program</a> (GitHub).
%e A396917 (164, 12, 56, 84, 176) is such a quintuple because sigma(164)^2 * psi(164) * phi(164) = 294^2 * 252 * 80 = 164^4 + 12^4 + 56^4 + 84^4 + 176^4.
